                            <comment id="184162" author="ofaaland" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2017 17:53:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello Minh,&lt;br/&gt;
This hasn&apos;t happened again to my knowledge.  Perhaps it was just a mail relay failure somewhere along the line.  You can close the ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="184152" author="mdiep" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2017 17:30:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ofaaland&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ofaaland&quot;&gt;ofaaland&lt;/a&gt;, do you still see this issue? I just check the LU project&apos;s notification, it should email to all watcher. Keep in mind you won&apos;t receive email for your own comments, it&apos;s per user setting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="147517" author="ofaaland" created="Fri, 1 Apr 2016 00:09:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello Andreas,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nope, the message is not in my spam or deleted folders nor just overlooked.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I definitely added myself as a watcher well before the comment referring to the patch.  I helped Cameron get the code where the NULL pointer dereference occurred, and added myself as a watcher within 2 hours of that.  That puts it at least 6 hours before Bobijam&apos;s comment was posted, based on the times reported when I hover over the comment heading in Jira.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-Olaf&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="147516" author="adilger" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2016 23:59:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Olaf, presumably the email was not in your spam folder or such?  Also, is there any chance that you added yourself as a watcher after the message was posted, but the time difference was due to a different time zone or similar?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="147491" author="jgmitter" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2016 19:56:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Olaf,&lt;br/&gt;
I have asked our infrastructure team to have a look at this issue for you.  I&apos;ll update the ticket when I receive a response.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks.&lt;br/&gt;
Joe&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
